1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§1, as corrected by RR 2017, c. 1, §22, is amended
3 to read:
4 1. Affordable housing. "Affordable housing" means a decent, safe and sanitary
5 dwelling, apartment or other living accommodation for a household whose income does
6 not exceed 80% of the median income for the area as defined by the United States
7 Department of Housing and Urban Development under the United States Housing Act of
8 1937, Public Law 75-412, 50 Stat. 888, Section 8, as amended has the same meaning as in
9 section 5246, subsection 1.
10 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 1989, c. 104, Pt. A, §45 and
11 Pt. C, §10 and amended by c. 562, §1, is further amended to read:
12 3. Comprehensive plan. "Comprehensive plan" means a document or interrelated
13 documents containing the elements established under section 4326, subsections 1 to 4,
14 including the strategies for an implementation program which that are consistent with the
15 procedures, goals and guidelines established under subchapter II 2.
16 Sec. 3. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§4-B, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 578, §2, is
17 repealed.
18 Sec. 4. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§5-B, ¶C, as enacted by PL 1999, c. 776, §7, is
19 amended to read:
20 C. Construction or, extension or upgrade of sewer, water and other utility lines
21 infrastructure;
